<h2>Resources in This Category</h2>
<ul>

    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://geography.about.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>About.com: Geography</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://geography.about.com/</strong></font> <br /> Includes atlas, countries, maps, quizzes, and facts. Also answers to FAQs.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://bartleby.com/151/zh.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Atlantic Ocean</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://bartleby.com/151/zh.html</strong></font> <br /> Provides facts about the second largest ocean including background, geography, economic significance, transportation.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/schools/barnabybear/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>BBC Barnaby Bear</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.bbc.co.uk/schools/barnabybear/</strong></font> <br /> Where in the world is Barnaby Bear? Games, stories, photographs and a scrapbook.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/scotland/education/sysm/landscapes/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>BBC Landscapes of Scotland</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.bbc.co.uk/scotland/education/sysm/landscapes/</strong></font> <br /> Develop map skills while exploring the highlands, central lowlands and islands of Scotland.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/schools/websites/11_16/site/geography.shtml" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>BBC Schools - Geography (11-16)</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.bbc.co.uk/schools/websites/11_16/site/geography.shtml</strong></font> <br /> List of geography websites for 11-16 year old students, including games and activities and resources for teaches and parents.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/schools/websites/4_11/site/geography.shtml" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>BBC Schools - Geography (4-11)</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.bbc.co.uk/schools/websites/4_11/site/geography.shtml</strong></font> <br /> List of geography websites for 4-11 year old students, including games and activities and resources for teaches and parents.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>CIA - The World Factbook</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/</strong></font> <br /> Features map and brief descriptions of the geography, people, government, economy, communications, transportation, military and transnational issues.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.citypopulation.de/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>City Population</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.citypopulation.de/</strong></font> <br /> Statistics and maps about the major population clusters of the world. Also information about the capitals and principal cities of many countries. In English and German.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.climate-zone.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Climate Zone</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.climate-zone.com/</strong></font> <br /> Climate information for cities and countries all over the world</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.studentsoftheworld.info/menu_infopays.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Countries of the World</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.studentsoftheworld.info/menu_infopays.html</strong></font> <br /> Cultural and geographical information about countries of the world through interactive maps.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.countriesquest.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Countries Quest</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.countriesquest.com/</strong></font> <br /> Features articles about different countries organized by continent. Offers information on natural resources, people, arts, economy, government, and history.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.countryscorecard.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Country Scorecard</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.countryscorecard.com/</strong></font> <br /> Choose a country and find statistics about its population, area, economy, health, and education. Includes images of flags.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.drivearoundtheworld.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Drive Around the World</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.drivearoundtheworld.com/</strong></font> <br /> Learn about this ambitious project to travel around the globe in order to raise money for Parkinson&#039;s disease research. Includes interactive map, daily journals, photos, and geographical facts.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.enchantedlearning.com/geography/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Enchanted Learning - Geography</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.enchantedlearning.com/geography/</strong></font> <br /> Collection of geography pages, printouts and activities for students.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.euratlas.net/geography/europe/index.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Euratlas: Physical atlas</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.euratlas.net/geography/europe/index.html</strong></font> <br /> Interactive map of Europe locating mountains, rivers, countries, and towns. Includes a map with links to photographs of the featured locations.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://school.discoveryeducation.com/schooladventures/geogame/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Geo Game</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://school.discoveryeducation.com/schooladventures/geogame/</strong></font> <br /> Offers adventures from around the globe.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.geographia.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Geographia</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.geographia.com/</strong></font> <br /> Provides information about the people, history, culture, natural terrain, and tourist attractions in Asia, Africa, Europe, Latin America, and the Caribbean.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.eduplace.com/geonet/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>GeoNet Kid's Place</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.eduplace.com/geonet/</strong></font> <br /> Explore the geography of the United States in this interactive game created for students.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.getty.edu/research/tools/vocabularies/tgn/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.getty.edu/research/tools/vocabularies/tgn/</strong></font> <br /> Searchable database of place names around the world tells where it is located. Includes more than a million ancient and contemporary names including variations.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.gb3pi.org.uk/great.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Great Circle Calculator</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.gb3pi.org.uk/great.html</strong></font> <br /> Features calculating direct line distances between any two points on the earth&#039;s globe.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.gcmap.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Great Circle Mapper</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.gcmap.com/</strong></font> <br /> Displays maps and computes distances along a geodesic path. Includes a searchable database of airports and other locations.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.lessontutor.com/ltpuzzlehome.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Lesson Tutor</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.lessontutor.com/ltpuzzlehome.html</strong></font> <br /> Features a selection of interactive puzzles on the states, countries, 13 colonies, capitals, and sign language finger spelling.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://lcweb2.loc.gov/frd/cs/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Library of Congress - Country Studies</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://lcweb2.loc.gov/frd/cs/</strong></font> <br /> Find in-depth information about everything from geography to weather, from government to religion, for more than 100 countries. Prepared by the Federal Research Division of the Library of Congress.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.humanitiesclub.talktalk.net/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Mr. S's Humanities Club</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.humanitiesclub.talktalk.net/</strong></font> <br /> Includes information about mountains, rivers, weather, Greece, links and software reviews.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.nationalgeographic.com/geobee/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>National Geographic - GeoBee Challenge</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.nationalgeographic.com/geobee/</strong></font> <br /> Online game changes every day with ten new geography questions.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.robertbremec.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Photo Diaries and Sketches</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.robertbremec.com/</strong></font> <br /> View photos taken from around the world during Robert Bremec&#039;s travels. Includes slideshow feature.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.sheppardsoftware.com/Geography.htm" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Sheppard Software - Geography Games</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.sheppardsoftware.com/Geography.htm</strong></font> <br /> Offers games which test geography of the world. Country names are spoken and brief descriptions are provided.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.lizardpoint.com/geography/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Test your Geography Knowledge</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.lizardpoint.com/geography/</strong></font> <br /> Contains quizzes on maps of continents, countries, and states.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.greatestplaces.org/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>The Greatest Places</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.greatestplaces.org/</strong></font> <br /> Explore seven of the most geographically dynamic locations on Earth. Learn about the Imax film, add your own favorite place, get a Greatest Places image, or check out the question of the week.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.funbrain.com/where/index.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Where is That</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.funbrain.com/where/index.html</strong></font> <br /> Maps and games for naming countries, states, and capitals. Also two player version.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/worldbalance/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>World in the Balance</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/worldbalance/</strong></font> <br /> Based on the NOVA educational TV program. Articles cover topics such as human consumption, sustainable population rate, and the impact of the average age within a country. Page includes people counter, photos, quizzes, and maps.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.yourchildlearns.com/monuments.htm" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>World Monuments Map Puzzle</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.yourchildlearns.com/monuments.htm</strong></font> <br /> Interactive puzzle for locations and significance of the cultural monuments of the world. Also printable map of continents. Requires Windows 95, 98 or 3.1.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.sheppardsoftware.com/web_games_trivia_world.htm" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>World Trivia Web Quizzes</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.sheppardsoftware.com/web_games_trivia_world.htm</strong></font> <br /> Learn fascinating facts about world countries. Each quiz selects 10 world trivia facts at random from a total set of 480.</p>
    </li>	
</ul>

